1. Added proper error handling around event listener operations
2. Added type safety checks for the event data
3. Added validation to ensure window.addEventListener exists before using it
4. Added try/catch blocks to prevent crashes from malformed event data
5. Added explicit boolean conversion for the available property
6. Added proper cleanup in the return function with error handling

These changes will prevent JavaScript errors that could prevent button initialization, especially in environments where the window object might not be fully initialized or where events might carry unexpected data.

